  • Method Details

    • getURIs

      @NonNull public List<URI> getURIs()
      Retrieve all URIs referenecd by this Asset Links tree. If isComplete(), this set represents the full Asset Links tree derived from the first entry in the returned list.
      Returns:
      a List of URIs in the order discovered. The first entry is the source URI for this Asset Links tree.

    • isComplete

      public boolean isComplete()
      Whether parsing has completed successfully (including the full tree of include directives). If isError() is true, this will always return false.
      Returns:
      true if parsing completed successfully, else false

    • isError

      public boolean isError()
      Whether an error was encountered during parsing. If this is true, no more parsing can occur, and any AssetLinksJSONParser.StatementMatcherCallback results should be ignored.
      Returns:
      true if an error was encountered during parsing, else false

    • isWarning

      public boolean isWarning()
      Whether any non-fatal parsing errors were encountered during parsing. If this is true, the parsing can still complete successfully, and the verification results can still be trusted. NOTE: this exists primarily to validate the behavior of this parser with the Asset Links compatibility test suite.
      Returns:
      true if any non-fatal parsing errors were encountered, else false

    • addStatementMatcher

      public void addStatementMatcher(@NonNull StatementMatcher statementMatcher, @NonNull AssetLinksJSONParser.StatementMatcherCallback callback)
      Add a StatementMatcher and corresponding AssetLinksJSONParser.StatementMatcherCallback to this AssetLinksJSONParser. All statement matchers should be added before start(URI) is called.
      Parameters:
      statementMatcher - the StatementMatcher to add
      callback - the AssetLinksJSONParser.StatementMatcherCallback to invoke when a match occurs

    • start

      @NonNull public URI start(@NonNull URI sourceURI)
      Start this AssetLinksJSONParser for the specified Asset Links URI
      Parameters:
      sourceURI - the initial Asset Links URI. It must be an absolute URI.
      Returns:
      the first URI to fetch for onDocumentLoaded(URI, String)

    • onDocumentLoaded

      @Nullable public URI onDocumentLoaded(@NonNull URI documentURI, @NonNull String document) throws AssetLinksJSONParser.IllFormattedStatementException, AssetLinksJSONParser.TooManyIncludesException, AssetLinksJSONParser.MatcherException
      This method should be invoked with the document contents for the URIs returned from start(URI) and onDocumentLoaded(URI, String). It will continue to return URIs until the entire Asset Links include tree has been parsed, or until a parsing error occurs.
      Parameters:
      documentURI - the URI for document
      document - a String containing the contents of document, interpreted as a UTF-8 string
      Returns:
      the next URI to fetch, or null if parsing is complete
      Throws:
      AssetLinksJSONParser.IllFormattedStatementException - if parsing fails due to a semantically invalid document
      AssetLinksJSONParser.TooManyIncludesException - if parsing fails due to exceeding the limit on the size of the Asset Links include tree
      AssetLinksJSONParser.MatcherException - if any registered StatementMatcher throws an exception
